Nigeria’s queen of daytime television Funmi Iyanda has returned with another talk show named Public Eye, which premieres today. Instead of television, the show will be on Instagram Live at 8 pm every Friday on @publiceyeng. Tonight’s exclusive features the Director-General of the Nigeria Center for Disease Control (NCDC) Dr Chikwe Ihekwazu, human rights activist, and Executive President, Women In Africa (WIA) Hafsat Abiola-Costello and strategic security and intelligence specialist Dr Kabir Adamu. Watch the video teaser for the show below: 